               <p>JOHN HEMRY. I witnessed this marriage - I remember the prisoner as the person married to Miss Elizabeth Whitehurst; she is now in court.</p>
               <p>Cross-examined by MR. ANDREWS. Q. Were you a friend of the parties? A. No; I am a publican, and live opposite to the church-gate - Jarvis ordered a breakfast at my house for four or five persons, but only himself and Whiteburst came: after breakfast, he said he was going to be married, and was in a difficulty about nobody coming to be witnesses, and asked if I would go over, which I did; I knew neither of them before - I asked him where the lady lived; he said in Windmill-street. Tottenham-court-road - I have seen her several times since.</p>
